• Steno order: STKPWHRAO*EUFRPBLGTSDZ
  • "Should The King PWlease Wear His Red And Orange STARry Elephant Underwear For Royal PWurposes Before Lunch Gets Totally Super Devoured (by) Zombies?"
  • F makes "f", "v", and "s" sounds
  • *F usually makes a "v" sound
  • *S occasionally makes a "st" sound when "ft" is unavailable
  • Short "i" sound = EU => I
  • Long "a" sound AEU
  • Long "ee" sound AOE
  • Long "i" sound AOEU => AOI
  • Long "oh" sound OE
  • "ew" or "oo" sound not spelled "oo" AOU
  • Long "a" = A + vowel keys on other side
  • Long "e" = E + vowel keys on other side
  • Long "i" = I + vowel keys on other side
  • Long "u" = U + vowel keys on other side
  • Long "o" = O + E
  • "aw" sound AU
  • "ow" sound OU
  • "oi" sound OEU
  • AE: words spelled with "ea"
  • AO: words spelled with "oo" or "oa"

  • . TP-PL => F-PL (full stop, spaced)
  • . P-P (decimal point, unspaced)
  • ... SKWR-RBGS => SY-SHUN (suspension point, then capital)
  • ... HR-PS => L-PS (ellipsis, then lowercase)
  • ? H-F (question mark, spaced)
  • ! SKHRAPL => SKLAM (exclamation mark, spaced)
  • ' A*E (opening single quote/apostrophe, no space)
  • ' AE (closing single quote/apostrophe, space)
  • " KW-GS => Q-SHUN (opening quotation mark, no space)
  • " KR-GS => C-SHUN (closing quotation mark, space)
  • , KW-BG (comma, spaced)
  • ; SKWR*RBGS or STPH*FPLT (semi-colon, spaced)
  • : STPH-FPLT (colon, spaced)
  • : KHR-PB => KL-N (colon, unspaced)
  • - H-PB => H-PB (hyphen), unspaced
  • -- TK-RB => D-SH (dash)
  • - PH*PBS => M-NS (minus, spaced)
  • + PHR*US => PL*US (plus)
  • = KWA*LS => QA*LS (unspaced equals)
  • = KW-L => Q-L (spaced equals)
  • * STA*R (star)
  • < AEPBGT or AEPBG => ANGT (opening angle bracket)
  • > A*EPBGT or A*EPBG => A*NGT (closing angle bracket)
  • < HR*PB => L*N (less than)
  • > TKPWR*PB => GR*N (greater than)
  • < PWRABG => BRAK (opening angle bracket)
  • > PWRA*BG => BRA*K (closing angle bracket)
  • ( PREPB => PREN (opening parenthesis)
  • ) PR*EPB => PR*EN (closing parenthesis)
  • [ PWR-BGT => BR-KT (opening bracket)
  • ] PWR*BGT => BR*KT (closing bracket)
  • { TPR-BGT => FR-KT (opening French bracket)
  • } TPR*BGT => FR*KT (closing French bracket)
  • / OEU (forward slash, unspaced)
  • \ SPWHRAERB => SBLAESH (backslash)
  • ~ T*LD (tilde, spaced)
  • ~ T*EULD (tilde, unspaced)
  • @ KWRAT => YAT (at-sign
  • # HAERB => HAESH (hash)
  • $ TK-PL => D-M (dollar mark)
  • % PERS (percent)
  • ^ KR-RT => C-RT (caret)
  • & SP-PBD => SP-ND (ampersand)
  • _ R*UPBD or RUPBD => RUND (underscore)
  • | PAO*EUP (pipe)
  • ` KH-FG => CH-VG (grave character, backwards)
  • ` TR-RL (opening backquote, grave brief inverted)
  • ` TR*RL (closing backquote, grave brief inverted)

Punctuation dictionary

  • . TP-PL => F-PL (full stop, spaced)
  • . P-P (decimal point, unspaced)
  • ... SKWR-RBGS => SY-SHUN (suspension point, then capital)
  • ... HR-PS => L-PS (ellipsis, then lowercase)
  • ? H-F (question mark, spaced)
  • ! SKHRAPL => SKLAM (exclamation mark, spaced)
  • ' A*E (opening single quote/apostrophe, no space)
  • ' AE (closing single quote/apostrophe, space)
  • " KW-GS => Q-SHUN (opening quotation mark, no space)
  • " KR-GS => C-SHUN (closing quotation mark, space)
  • , KW-BG (comma, spaced)

  • + PHR*US => PL*US (plus)
  • = KWA*LS => QA*LS (unspaced equals)
  • = KW-L => Q-L (spaced equals)
  • * STA*R (star)
  • < AEPBGT or AEPBG => ANGT (opening angle bracket)
  • > A*EPBGT or A*EPBG => A*NGT (closing angle bracket)

  • > TKPWR*PB => GR*N (greater than)
  • < PWRABG => BRAK (opening angle bracket)
  • > PWRA*BG => BRA*K (closing angle bracket)
  • ( PREPB => PREN (opening parenthesis)
  • ) PR*EPB => PR*EN (closing parenthesis)
  • [ PWR-BGT => BR-KT (opening bracket)
  • ] PWR*BGT => BR*KT (closing bracket)
  • { TPR-BGT => FR-KT (opening French bracket)

Punctuation dictionary

  • # and one of STPHAOFPLT for single digits
  • Stroke two single-digit numbers together for two-digit numbers
  • Include EU to invert steno order
  • Include D to duplicate numbers
  • Include Z for hundreds
  • Include DZ for hundreds of dollars
  • Include K or -BG => -K for clock time
  • Add /#OZ to append "00"
  • # and one of STPHAOFPLT for single digits
  • Stroke two single-digit numbers together for two-digit numbers
  • Include EU to invert steno order
  • Include 0EU for (some) fractions
  • Include D to duplicate numbers
  • Include Z for hundreds
  • Include DZ for hundreds of dollars
  • Include K or -BG => -K for clock time
  • Add /#OZ to append "00"
